text:
State Budget 2020: What Revenue and Expenditure Increased Before Second Reading?

05 Nov 2019, 16:15


Today the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine presented the draft law "On the State Budget of Ukraine for 2020", which was finalized for the second reading. A number of changes were made to the document

This was reported by the press service of the Ministry of Finance.
According to the report, the state budget revenues (excluding transfers) for 2020 are proposed to increase by UAH 14.18 billion, including the general fund by UAH 11.9 billion and the special fund by UAH 2.3 billion. The deficit will be 2.09% of GDP. Expenditures of the revised draft budget increased to UAH 1 180.1 billion.
It is noted that the document is balanced and aimed at solving urgent issues and implementing the Program of Activities of the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine. First of all, there will be an increase in the cost of addressing urgent issues, both social and economic.
In particular, increased revenues and expenses for:
- providing schools with the necessary equipment - UAH 3.5 billion;
- Improvement of social protection of certain categories of pedagogical workers of general secondary education institutions provides for a subsidy - UAH 3.8 billion;
- creation of educational and practical centers of modern vocational education increased by 159 million UAH;
- Assistance to families with children - by UAH 2.2 billion;
- design, construction and repair works, purchase of housing and premises for the development of family and other forms of education and provision of orphaned children - by UAH 364.1 million;
- assistance to single pensioners - by UAH 860 million;
- centralized procurement of medicines and medical devices for the treatment of certain diseases - by UAH 3.2 billion;
- modernization and updating of the material and technical base of multidisciplinary intensive care hospitals - by UAH 1 billion;
- treatment of Ukrainian citizens abroad - by UAH 400 million;
- implementation of measures of socio-economic development of the territories - UAH 2 billion;
- construction, reconstruction, repair and maintenance of public roads of local importance, streets and roads of communal property in settlements - by 1.5 million UAH.
- construction and reconstruction of bridges - by UAH 500 million;
- conducting land inventory and updating the cartographic basis of the State Land Cadastre - by UAH 291.9 million;
- withdrawal of state-owned coal mining enterprises at break-even level - by UAH 622.8 million;
- the program "Crosslinking of the country - a project of youth mobility" - 500 million UAH;
- for the creation of the Museum of Contemporary Art of Ukraine - UAH 54 million;
- International Children's Center "Artek" - for 9,8 million UAH.
Expenditures on national security and defense amount to UAH 245.8 billion, in particular:
- cash and wages (with accruals) - UAH 141.4 billion (+ UAH 14.4 billion by 2019);
- medicines and dressings - UAH 657.8 million (+ UAH 82.8 million by 2019);
- food - UAH 4.84 billion (+ UAH 248.1 million by 2019);
- payment for utilities and energy - UAH 4.9 billion (+ UAH 510.7 million by 2019);
- Creation, purchase, modernization and repair of weapons and military (special) equipment - UAH 35.4 billion (+ UAH 7.8 billion by 2019);
- payment of lump sum financial assistance in case of death (death), disability or partial disability and other social payments - UAH 6.66 billion (+ UAH 2.44 billion by 2019);
- Construction (purchase) of housing - UAH 2.23 billion (UAH +389.8 million by 2019).
In addition, it is noted that the national debt in UAH equals UAH 2 045.1 billion and will make up 45.3% of the projected GDP. The volume of payments for the repayment of the national debt for 2020 is projected to amount to UAH 282.1 billion, including the repayment of the public external debt - UAH 120.3 billion, the state domestic debt - UAH 161.9 billion. Payments for public debt servicing for 2020 are estimated at UAH 141.5 billion. Privatization proceeds increased by UAH 7 billion, which will reduce planned borrowing.
We will remind, Alexey Goncharuk said that in the budget for 2020 the government does not look for additional resources in raising taxes, and proposes to reduce administrative expenses and to service the government and central executive bodies by an average of 10%.
Goncharuk also called new figures for the state budget for 2020.

